The All Progressives Congress (APC) will on Thursday, March 17 meet for an emergency National Executive Committee (NEC) meeting. The meeting which will be held at 11:00 am virtually is expected to discuss the convention scheduled for March 26 and other party-related issues. This is contained in a notice of meeting signed by Gov. Abubakar Bello, the acting Chairman of the APC Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee; Sen. Ken Nnamani (South-East), Mrs Stella Okotete (National Women Leader), Sen. Aba Ali (North-West) and Prof. Tahir Mamman (North-East). Umahi Vows To Deal With Ebonyi PDP, Says Buni Remains APC… 2023 Presidency: Why Nigerians’ll Give PDP Second Chance –… The decision to hold the meeting was taken at the 23rd meeting of the committee on Tuesday. The meeting, they said, is pursuant to Article 25B (i and ii) of the Party Constitution, and by the power vested on the Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) via the NEC resolution of Dec. 8, 2020. “The communique partlyread, “The CECPC of the party at its 23rd meeting of 8th March 2022, hereby calls for the meeting of the National Executive Committee (NEC) of our great Party, the All Progressives Congress (APC) to consider matters pertaining to the national convention, governance of the party and any other relevant business of the party.” All members of the NEC are by this invitation to take notice of the meeting in accordance with article 12.3.”